    <item>
      <title>Five Old Walls - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 19 Sep 2025 02:16:59 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13624" class="post-13624 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Five Old Walls&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I received a letter from Monty in the mail. No, it wasn&amp;#8217;t a goodbye letter, he was just thanking me for the medicine I gave him last week. He also sent me a gift: a trash bin. Wow, thanks. 🗑️&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Saharah was out in the rain, looking for old wallpaper, so I started asking around for some. Antonio was the first one to sniff out a good one for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/Array" alt="Antonio: that old wallpaper...is super dusty. Don't unroll it, up my nose!" class="wp-image-13626" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rosie also had some old wallpaper for me, and she called Saharah &amp;#8220;a kick in the pants.&amp;#8221; 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/Array" alt="Rosie: Oh yeah! I totally heard that Saharah was in town! She's seriously a kick in the pants, la-di-da!" class="wp-image-13627" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Felicity asked me for a new greeting, and I rarely bother with those (unlike catchphrases). But I decided to give it a try this time, and I told her to say &amp;#8220;Ow! You bit me!&amp;#8221; 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/Array" alt="Felicity: Ow! You bit me!! Like, look at me! I'm happy!" class="wp-image-13625" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As I continued asking for more old wallpaper, I was surprised by all the help I was getting. Mint, Marina, and Fang all helped me out too! That&amp;#8217;s a total of five out of my nine villagers! I believe that ties a record; I&amp;#8217;ve also received five walls/carpets on two previous occasions since starting this blog, most recently in &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2016/05/04/carpet-givers/"&gt;2016&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I took three of the old wallpapers over to Saharah, and she gave me a tropical vista. I put the other two in storage for next time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, Mint met me outside my house and immediately wanted to play a game of hide-and-seek. She gave me 15 minutes to find her, Rosie, and Marina. I took my time, and I first found Marina hiding behind a tree near Antonio&amp;#8217;s house. A couple minutes later, I found Rosie behind a tree near the fountain.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/Array" alt="Rosie: Come on! This is hide-and-seek, not...um... hide-and-do-nothing!" class="wp-image-13628" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I &lt;em&gt;am &lt;/em&gt;seeking, and I found you, so what&amp;#8217;s the issue?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mint took me the longest to find, but it was only due to her being the farthest away. It definitely wasn&amp;#8217;t the quality of her hiding spot&amp;#8230; 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/Array" alt="Mint tries to hide behind a sign post." class="wp-image-13629" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mint was impressed with my win, and she gave me a mega plinkoid as my prize.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/Array" alt="Mint: Amazing! Wow, I might have to rethink my notions of you, it's minty!" class="wp-image-13630" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Antonio asked me to deliver a gift to Fang, and I was happy to help out. Antonio rewarded me with a library wall, although I&amp;#8217;m not sure I want to use it after hearing this&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/Array" alt="Antonio: This library wall is for you. Don't worry, I gave it a good wipe down, up my nose." class="wp-image-13631" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I noticed a new hybrid today (a purple tulip) in the same area where those purple roses disappeared from last week. The rain I got yesterday must&amp;#8217;ve helped it out. 🙂&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Nana&amp;#8217;s replacement has not moved in yet, but I expect that to happen the next time I play.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/18/five-old-walls/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-18T22:16:59-04:00"&gt;September 18, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-18T22:24:57-04:00"&gt;September 18, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/RUU_8352-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Name That Tune - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8366" class="post-8366 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Name That Tune&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Saharah was in town on Wednesday, and I helped her out with a couple of deliveries. I took carpet packages to Blathers and Pelly (for Phyllis) for her. Saharah rewarded me with a blue tarp.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Caroline told me that she found Blathers sleeping standing up in the museum (not a surprise). She also mentioned that he can spin his head in crazy directions.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/Array" alt="Caroline: On top of that, he can spin his head in all sorts of crazy directions!" class="wp-image-8367" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I knew real owls could do that, but it would be funny if Blathers actually did that in the game. 🦉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Filbert asked me for a fossil &amp;#8220;with legs&amp;#8221; (because of his catchphrase), so I gave him a dimetrodon torso. He was very happy with it, and he put it on display right away.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/Array" alt="Filbert: It's the smell of...history! It's so cool, with legs!" class="wp-image-8368" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He thanked me with a lunar rover, which is a pretty cool reward.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, it was raining in town. Truffles randomly announced that she&amp;#8217;s not into judo when it rains. I&amp;#8217;m pretty sure she&amp;#8217;s not into judo when it&amp;#8217;s dry either, so I don&amp;#8217;t quite understand her point. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/Array" alt="Truffles: Helloooooo! Know what? When it's raining, I'm just not into judo..." class="wp-image-8369" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today is La-Di-Day, the day villagers will sing songs in hopes of having their song being chosen as the new town tune. Drift was the first to sing to me&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/Array" alt="Drift: This little song is about how real men love to walk around!" class="wp-image-8376" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, his song didn&amp;#8217;t stand out to me. I didn&amp;#8217;t hire him, but Whitney was also nearby&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/Array" alt="Whitney: You're about to hear a singing sensation live! Whitney, all night!" class="wp-image-8370" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She sang the Mario theme for me, and I hired her&amp;#8230;even though I&amp;#8217;ve used the Mario song as my town tune before. However, I didn&amp;#8217;t keep it very long. Robin also performed a song for me, and it sounded familiar (though I&amp;#8217;m not sure what it was). I hired her, and her mystery song is now Forest&amp;#8217;s town tune.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/Array" alt="Robin: Yeah, I guess it's totally obvious. I'm the Melody Queen of this town!" class="wp-image-8371" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;A few minutes later, a 4th animal sang to me&amp;#8230;but not for a town tune. It was K.K. Slider, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Dirge&amp;#8221; for me at the Roost. I guess we are getting closer to Halloween time, after all.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Dirge!" class="wp-image-8372" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Filbert came down with a cold, so I gave him some medicine Thursday and again tonight. Get well soon, little guy!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I wrapped up my night at town hall, where I checked out the notes for the new town tune.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/Array" alt="My new town tune, courtesy of Robin." class="wp-image-8373" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If any of you want to try it out, feel free! Of course, town tunes work in any Animal Crossing game, not just Wild World. Maybe you&amp;#8217;ll recognize what it&amp;#8217;s from!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/13/name-that-tune/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-13T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;September 13, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-14T00:07:19-04:00"&gt;September 14, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/caroline-spin.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>5 Roses, 1 Monkey Gone - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 13 Sep 2025 01:50:55 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13613" class="post-13613 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;5 Roses, 1 Monkey Gone&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, I was surprised to find Nana packed up in boxes. She&amp;#8217;s leaving, without any advance warning.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/Array" alt="Nana: I think you can tell by looking, but I've decided to move out of Forest for good, banana man." class="wp-image-13614" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll miss her. It&amp;#8217;s too bad it wasn&amp;#8217;t my other monkey (Monty) moving out instead.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I went over a whole week without playing, after generally playing 3+ days a week during most of the summer. So when I got around to this part of town, I was a bit surprised to find that my five purple roses were all gone. Here are the before-and-after photos:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="553" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/Array" alt="A comparison of my flowers on September 1st vs. September 9th. Five purple roses were all gone." class="wp-image-13615" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Hybrids seem more likely to not survive if you go more than a week without playing. If you want to keep any hybrids during a break from the game, you&amp;#8217;ll need to put them in your house (or in storage).&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Antonio told me that his memory is getting bad, so he keeps his essential items in his gym bag. That includes his sunglasses, his lifting gloves, and&amp;#8230;a &lt;em&gt;ribbon on a stick?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/Array" alt="Antonio: You never know when someone's gonna jump out and challenge you to a rhythmic-gymnastics duel!" class="wp-image-13616" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I received Nana&amp;#8217;s goodbye letter in the mail. She just &lt;em&gt;peeled &lt;/em&gt;out of town and &lt;em&gt;split&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/Array" alt="Dearest Jeff, I'm leaving Forest today... I know it's the right step, but I'm still sad, because I'll be leaving you. I hope I see you again someday. Signed, -Nana" class="wp-image-13617" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I found Rosie holding her watering can, standing up against the wall of Nook &amp;#8216;n&amp;#8217; Go. She said she&amp;#8217;s really focused on her watering routine, and she may even have a watering addiction. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/Array" alt="Rosie: I think I have a watering addiction, la-di-da." class="wp-image-13618" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I don&amp;#8217;t know why she&amp;#8217;s telling me all this. I guess she&amp;#8217;s just pouring her heart out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Monty has come down with a cold, so I gave him some medicine yesterday and again today. Get well soon, Monty! (So you can leave next.) 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I listened in a conversation between Biskit and Felicity, and it was the one where Felicity wanted to charge a rental fee to Biskit for borrowing a DVD. But Felicity&amp;#8217;s catchphrase (&amp;#8220;528 bells&amp;#8221;) just added to the confusion when Biskit wanted to know the cost. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/Array" alt="Felicity: Let's see, at the low, low price of 500 bells a day, that would be...like...3500 bells, 528 bells!" class="wp-image-13619" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Pascal was in town today, but I couldn&amp;#8217;t find a scallop to give him (even after saving/quitting and restarting a few times). So I just had a chat with him anyway, and he told me that the final shape of an object is what decides its known form? I&amp;#8217;ve seen this line before, but I still have no idea what it means. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/Array" alt="Pascal: The final shape of an object is what decides its known form, maaaan." class="wp-image-13620" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll be back next week with another entry, so I hope you&amp;#8217;ll return to see who replaces Nana. Who do you think I&amp;#8217;ll get? I hope it&amp;#8217;s someone good!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/12/roses-monkey-gone/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-12T21:50:55-04:00"&gt;September 12, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-12T21:55:15-04:00"&gt;September 12, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/RUU_8346-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Go With the Flow - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/12/go-with-the-flow/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/12/go-with-the-flow/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 13 Sep 2025 00:36:50 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8974" class="post-8974 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Go With the Flow&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;I don&amp;#8217;t know if I&amp;#8217;ve mentioned this before, but I typically deposit bells in multiples of 10,000 bells each day when I visit Resident Services. So if I have 33,000 bells, for example, I&amp;#8217;ll put 30k into savings and just carry the 3,000. But on Monday, I only had 26 bells leftover in my pockets. So when I went into the Roost to buy some coffee for a Nook Miles+ goal, I couldn&amp;#8217;t afford it!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/12/go-with-the-flow/Array" alt="Brewster: Coo! You're a little short on cash... Sorry, but...I don't run tabs..." class="wp-image-8975" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So I went back outside and shook a few trees until two of them gave me the bells I needed for my coffee. ☕&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, I found Truffles the pig at the campsite. She was staring at me pretty intently. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/12/go-with-the-flow/Array" alt="Truffles, at the campsite: Hi there! I'm Truffles! I'm here on a camping trip! You live on this island? Tres cool." class="wp-image-8976" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I already have Truffles in my &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/"&gt;Wild World&lt;/a&gt; town, and one Truffles is more than enough. Besides, I don&amp;#8217;t want to &lt;em&gt;hog &lt;/em&gt;up all the Truffles&amp;#8230;es in the world. 🐷&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Ketchup told me she wanted to go see the world to learn how to become famous.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/12/go-with-the-flow/Array" alt="Ketchup: I've got to see the world! I've got to learn how to be famous!" class="wp-image-8977" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As much as I like Ketchup, I also don&amp;#8217;t want my island to become stagnant. And Ketchup has had a nice long stay in Forest (3.5 years), so I decided to let her go&amp;#8230;with the flow. (Sorry if this is a &lt;em&gt;jarring &lt;/em&gt;revelation.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, I went into her house for the last time to say goodbye. I&amp;#8217;ll soon be all out of Ketchup.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/12/go-with-the-flow/Array" alt="Ketchup: I'm, like, low-key worried that everyone's going to suffer from Ketchup deficiency..." class="wp-image-8978" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So long, Ketchup! I&amp;#8217;ll miss you, but maybe we&amp;#8217;ll meet again someday! Over burgers, perhaps.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Label was in town, and I realized I&amp;#8217;ve been ignoring her for months. So I decided to check in with her for a change. She wanted to see me in something professional, like a work outfit. She gave me a western shirt to use as an example, but I instead went with a pilot&amp;#8217;s uniform and captain&amp;#8217;s hat. Label loved it, and she gave me some Labelle tights.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/12/go-with-the-flow/Array" alt="Label hands me some tights." class="wp-image-8979" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Anyway, I&amp;#8217;ll have to go villager hunting tomorrow. I&amp;#8217;ll probably do my usual thing: I&amp;#8217;ll take five (or so) Nook Miles tickets and see if I can find anyone good. If not, I may roll the dice and risk a random villager. I&amp;#8217;ll be posting a new New Horizons Moments video soon, so maybe I&amp;#8217;ll reveal my next villager there. Keep an eye out for that!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Sunday, Wisp gave me a DJ&amp;#8217;s turntable.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Monday, I sold 16 bugs (mostly wasps) to Flick for exactly 75,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Tuesday, I sold 8 fish to C.J. for 112,125 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped Gulliver out on Wednesday, and he sent me a turban in the mail.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/12/go-with-the-flow/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-12T20:36:50-04:00"&gt;September 12, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-12T20:39:10-04:00"&gt;September 12, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/brewster-tabs-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Fish and Junk - Jeff&amp;#039;s Animal Crossing Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-6028" class="post-6028 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Fish and Junk&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Last Wednesday (September 3rd), Belle started complimenting my eyes. First, she said they were pretty&amp;#8230;but then she changed it to &amp;#8220;intense.&amp;#8221; &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Belle: Jeff, you've got really pretty eyes! No, that's not the right word... What is it? Intense? Yeah...intense!" class="wp-image-6029" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She said I had the eyes of a wrestler, and said they&amp;#8217;re not the eyes of someone who does a lot of thinking! Wow, I &lt;em&gt;think &lt;/em&gt;that&amp;#8217;s rude. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Belle: Yeah! They're not the eyes of someone who does a lot of thinking." class="wp-image-6030" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That made me &lt;em&gt;wrestle &lt;/em&gt;with the idea of tipping her over, but then she&amp;#8217;d be crying over spilled milk. (Just kidding. Be nice to cows.) 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Early September is the best time of year for &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/guides/ac/september-fishing.htm"&gt;ocean fishing&lt;/a&gt;, since there are no sea bass (or jellyfish) in sight. &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2024/09/04/million-bell-night/"&gt;Last year&lt;/a&gt;, I waited for a rainy day and then fished for two hours to make a million bells in one night. I didn&amp;#8217;t want to do that this time, though. Instead, I played (and fished) a little bit each day. I&amp;#8217;ll recap how it all went later in the entry.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Last Thursday, Static informed me that I was looking as awful as ever. (My villagers all seem to love me so much.) He gave me a misty shirt to wear instead, and I decided to put it on. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I found Gulliver down on the beach, and he gave me a gift and said I wouldn&amp;#8217;t find anything like it anywhere.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Gulliver: You won't find another like it anywhere! At least, I don't think you will..." class="wp-image-6031" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But it was a matryoshka, so I &lt;em&gt;did &lt;/em&gt;find something like it&amp;#8230;right inside the first one! 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As I was speaking with Kody near the wishing well, Tom came up and his face passed right through Kody&amp;#8217;s umbrella. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Tom's head passed through Kody's umbrella as Kody says: I'll train even harder, so that I bring more sunshine for us." class="wp-image-6032" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Sunday (September 7th), I received a goodbye letter in the mail from Mitzi. I&amp;#8217;m sad to see her go, but I&amp;#8217;m used to this happening. The revolving door of Animal Crossing on GameCube goes round and round.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Jeff, FYI: I recently decided to move for reasons I prefer not to go into. I can't tell you where I'm going, but I will say this: I won't forget you! Best of luck--to both of us. Goodbye! -Mitzi" class="wp-image-6033" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I found a note on the message board about a buried treasure in Acre D-1. Even though I didn&amp;#8217;t specifically seek it out, I didn&amp;#8217;t notice anything out of the ordinary when I passed through there. More on this later, though.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="To the folks of Forest. I buried valuable treasure somewhere in Acre D-1! Take a peek out there--maybe you'll find it... -from Puck" class="wp-image-6034" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tom said that Genji told him about money trees. He asked if I knew about them, and I said yes. So he wanted me to tell him about them, but all of the options were variations of &amp;#8220;no.&amp;#8221; I said &amp;#8220;that&amp;#8217;s my secret,&amp;#8221; and he started crying!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Tom: Why?! Why won't you tell me!? Haven't I been good to you!? See what you've done! You've made me cry, dang it!" class="wp-image-6035" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;m not sure what the big deal was, because he supposedly knew about them from Genji! 🤷‍♂️&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Anyway, I&amp;#8217;ve continued fishing most days lately, and the dump has been filling up with the junk I&amp;#8217;ve caught from the ocean. Here&amp;#8217;s how the dump looked Sunday (before the Monday pick-up).&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Nine heaps of trash in the dump." class="wp-image-6036" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Over by the wishing well today, Ursala said she found my blue bench for me. But she then took &lt;strong&gt;half the money in my pockets&lt;/strong&gt; as her reward! That was over 17,000 bells!!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Ursala: Oh, you have only 17,351 bells with you?! Wow, no morals, no cash... You're really depressing." class="wp-image-6037" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I didn&amp;#8217;t have any pitfalls with me, so I started pushing her around and I hit her with a net. Villagers shouldn&amp;#8217;t be allowed to just reach in and take our money. 😡&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Ursala: ....... You filthy ogre! I hope you get stung by a thousand bees!" class="wp-image-6038" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mitzi&amp;#8217;s replacement moved in today, and it&amp;#8217;s Hazel the squirrel! She&amp;#8217;s cute! 😊&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Hazel: So...are you new in town? How splendid! Would you... Uh... Would you like to be friends with me?" class="wp-image-6039" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;While walking around the museum, I fell into a pitfall behind the museum that was completely out of sight! I checked my map, and it was in Acre D-1. &lt;em&gt;This &lt;/em&gt;is the &amp;#8220;buried treasure&amp;#8221; that Puck left for me! Thanks a lot, old friend.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After some more fishing tonight, I noticed my savings balance was just 85k from a big milestone. So I went back out to fill up my pockets a couple more times. When I was done, my balance reached 25 million bells!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/Array" alt="Pelly: Your balance is 25,000,000 bells." class="wp-image-6040" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That meant I earned over 1.2 million bells just in the past week or so. I&amp;#8217;d call that a productive September fishing season!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;See you all next time. Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/09/08/fish-and-junk/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-08T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;September 8, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-09T01:48:51-04:00"&gt;September 9, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ac-belle-eyes1-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Salmon Recipes - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 07 Sep 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8962" class="post-8962 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Salmon Recipes&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Now that September is here, many valuable summer bugs and fish are out of season. That&amp;#8217;s disappointing, but I realized I had never cooked two of the food recipes that require salmon. Now that salmon have returned this month, I was able to get those done.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/Array" alt="Poke. Ingredients: Salmon, tomato." class="wp-image-8964" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I made some poke, and I also made a salmon sandwich that I gave to Ankha. She loved it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/Array" alt="Ankha: Thanks so much, darling. My tummy thanks you as well, I hate it!" class="wp-image-8965" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She gave me a shop uniform shirt to thank me.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, Pascal popped up from under the sea to ask me for a scallop. I gave him one, and he told me some words of wisdom about music just being air that&amp;#8217;s dancing.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/Array" alt="Pascal: Music is just air gettin' its dance on, maaan. We're all breathing shy songs that want to cut a rug." class="wp-image-8966" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He gave me a pearl for the scallop.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, Static was telling me about his journal that he writes in. He said when he doesn&amp;#8217;t have anything in particular to write down, he just jots down some puns! No wonder I like him so much!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/Array" alt="Static: If I got nothin' to write about, some nights I'll just jot down a few choice puns, in my tail." class="wp-image-8967" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Sounds like something I would do!&lt;br&gt;Just&amp;#8230;without the tail.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Hans the abominable snowman was camping at the campsite for the 2nd time. But I still was not interested in having him chill in Forest.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/Array" alt="Hans: Hey, you're a local, right? The name's Hans." class="wp-image-8968" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, it was raining when I started up the game. But it stopped within minutes, and a bit later, I spotted a rainbow in the sky! This was my 3rd rainbow I&amp;#8217;ve seen in Forest.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/Array" alt="Posing with a rainbow." class="wp-image-8969" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tonight, K.K. Slider was in town for his weekly show. I asked him for a random song, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Mambo&amp;#8221; for me and June.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/Array" alt="K.K.: right on. I'm tuned up and ready to roll. Who's in the mood for a little K.K. Mambo?" class="wp-image-8963" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Monday, I sold 32 bugs to Flick for 258,750 bells. That will probably be my last huge haul for him until next summer.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Wednesday, I returned a lost item to Merengue. She rewarded me with a suspender outfit.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped out Gullivarrr yesterday, and he sent me a sea captain&amp;#8217;s coat.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Today, Louie was sick with a cold. I gave him some medicine, and he handed over a flashy jacket in return.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Enjoy the rest of your weekend, and I&amp;#8217;ll see you all next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/06/salmon-recipes/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-06T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;September 6, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-07T00:30:06-04:00"&gt;September 7, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
